8jtto.question: With RTO selected, the system will automatically apply maximum brake pressure when the thrust levers have been retarded to idle with speed at or above 90 kts.

options.text: True
False

1z32xj.question: If both normal and alternative brake system pressure is lost it is still possible to use the brakes to bring the aircraft to a complete stop after landing?

options.text: True
False

qq1fq.question: Which hydraulic system operates the parking brake?

options.text: Hydraulic system A
Hydraulic system B
All of the above.
Brake accumulator

3vhlb.question: How far must you pull the emergency gear release handle before the related landing gear uplock is released?

options.text: Released as soon as handle pulled.
Approximately 61cm
Approximately 16cm
Approximately 6cm.

k66i4.question: You select the AUTO BRAKE to RTO on the ground, and the AUTO BRAKE DISARM light illuminates for 2 seconds then extinguishes.  What is the fault?

options.text: Autobrake is unavailable.
The system has passed the self test and there is NO fault.
You do not have the parking brake set.
The Auto Brake has failed the self test and should be re-cycled to off then back to RTO, if the light does not illuminate this time the system is serviceable.

e586i.question: Which of the following statements are false for Antiskid Protection.

options.text: All of the above are false.
The Antiskid system provides skid, locked wheel, touchdown and hydroplane protection in both normal and alternate braking.
Each wheel is provided with individual Antiskid protection in normal and alternate braking
Antiskid protection is provided for both normal and alternate brake systems.

2epsn.question: The landing gear lights on the main centre panel all indicate green, but the lights on the aft overhead panel show the LEFT GEAR is not locked and down.   You can ignore this situation as one green light, on either panel, for each landing gear, means the gear is down and locked.

options.text: True
False

xnxi2.question: Other than moving the Autobrake selector to OFF, how else can Autobraking be cancelled?

options.text: Applying manual brakes
Advancing forward thrust levers immediately after touchdown or Applying manual brakes
Applying manual brakes, Moving Speed Brake lever to DOWN detent or Advancing forward thrust levers immediately after touchdown.
Applying manual brakes or Moving Speed Brake lever to DOWN detent.

j97fd.question: Which of the following statements are true for the Nose Wheel Steering system

options.text: If alternate nose wheel steering is activated then the standby hydraulic system operates the nose wheel steering.

If alternate nose wheel steering is activated then the standby hydraulic system operates the nose wheel steering and as well as being in the down position, the nose landing gear must be compressed for nose wheel steering to be available.
Nose wheel steering is normally powered by hydraulic system A and as well as being in the down position, the nose landing gear must be compressed for nose wheel steering to be available.

Nose wheel steering is normally powered by hydraulic system A, If alternate nose wheel steering is activated then the standby hydraulic system operates the nose wheel steering and As well as being in the down position, the nose landing gear must be compressed for nose wheel steering to be available.

dvgqi.question: Which of the following statements is true, when the landing gear Manual Extension Access Door is open?

options.text: Normal landing gear extension is possible if Hydraulic system A operational.
The landing gear cannot be retracted.
The landing gear can be manually lowered with the lnding gear lever in ANY position.
All of the above are true
